<HEADLINE>
<P>
IKE'S WARNING ON MILITARY SPENDING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In the midst of the insanity now going on, along comes Willens with a breath of 
fresh air. The crushing budget negotiations could easily have been resolved by 
further reductions in the military but for our precipitous, saber-rattling 
excursion into the Persian Gulf. 
</P>
<P>
Having long ago appointed ourselves as world policemen, we continue to maintain 
bloated troops and equipment around the globe, meanwhile living beyond our 
means. And why didn't we send troops and equipment already under arms in 
Europe, Japan, Korea, etc. to the gulf? 
</P>
<P>
Eisenhower warned us of the evils of the military-industrial complex long ago. 
Let us wise up and insist on more realistic cutbacks to finally rid us of this 
cancer in our society. The Japanese and West Germans are not doing too badly 
following such sane policies. 
</P>
<P>
SANDY ELSTER, Venice 
</P>
</TEXT>
