</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A drug used to reduce the risk of recurrences in about half of breast cancer 
patients may also help the other half, as well as people with other types of 
cancer, researchers said. A new study by Dr. Michael Pollak, an assistant 
professor of oncology and medicine at McGill University in Montreal, published 
in the Journal of the National Cancer Institute, found the drug, tamoxifen, 
apparently reduces levels of a protein that promotes the growth of cancer 
cells. 
