test -- accidentally plowed his car through a wall into a DMV office in Canoga 
Park. The man, who has an unblemished driving record, and six others were hurt 
as the vehicle careened through a waiting area, stopping 30 feet inside. 
Passersby, above, peered at the damage.; Photo, DMV facility in Canoga Park had 
an unexpected entrance when John Anderson of Reseda accidentally drove his car 
in.; Photo, (Ventura County Edition, B10) Passersby inspect damage from crash. 
None of the injuries were life-threatening, authorities said. RICHARD DERK / 
Los Angeles Times; Photo, (Ventura County Edition, B6) John Anderson rests in 
the office after the accident. He was slightly bruised. 
</P>
