<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: WOMAN PLEADS NOT GUILTY IN KILLING OF HER 
MOTHER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A woman pleaded not guilty Tuesday to shooting and stabbing her mother to death 
in a slaying in La Canada Flintridge that also allegedly involved the suspect's 
11-year-old son. 
</P>
<P>
Victoria Madeira, 43, of Anaheim entered a plea of not guilty to the Oct. 14 
killing of Roma Jaul Jacobs, 78, and was ordered by a Municipal Court judge to 
return Nov. 27 for a pretrial hearing. 
</P>
<P>
Jacobs was attacked as she sought help by telephone. Madeira was dressed in 
combat fatigues and her son was wearing girl's clothing when deputies arrested 
them in the back yard of the dead woman's home. The boy previously pleaded not 
guilty to murder. 
</P>
