<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: VENTURA; 
</P>
<P>
COUNCIL DELAYS VOTE ON HOUSING PROJECT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SANTIAGO O'DONNELL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Ventura City Council has postponed a decision on a 147-unit affordable 
housing project in east Ventura after the panel discovered that the developer 
has been involved in significant litigation in recent years. 
</P>
<P>
The council voted unanimously Monday to postpone until Nov. 17 a decision on 
the project to give the developer, Ernest T. Mansi of Oxnard, a chance to 
explain why he was involved in so many lawsuits. 
</P>
<P>
The project by KNM Development Inc., which Mansi heads, had been tentatively 
approved Oct. 15 but was sent back to the planning staff for minor redesign. 
</P>
<P>
Since then, the council learned that Mansi had been involved in at least 10 
lawsuits in the last six years concerning development projects in Ventura and 
Santa Barbara counties, Ventura Mayor Richard Francis said. 
</P>
<P>
Francis said he was especially concerned about two nursing home projects, one 
is Lompoc and one in Santa Paula, that were never completed, and the collapse 
of a roof in a condominium project in Oxnard. Mansi did the engineering studies 
on the Oxnard project. 
</P>
<P>
Mansi was present Monday for the hearing but declined to make any comment. 
SANTIAGO O'DONNELL 
</P>
</TEXT>
