<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mando Ramos, twice the world lightweight boxing champion, is in serious 
condition at Long Beach Memorial Medical Center, where he is undergoing an 
evaluation of his heart, a hospital spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
Ramos, 41, of Westminster, was admitted to the hospital's intensive care ward 
Sunday. He won his first title at 20 in 1969, lost the championship in 1970 and 
won it again in 1972. 
</P>
