<P>
MERTES LEADS PIERCE TO VOLLEYBALL VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lori Mertes had 10 kills, eight blocks and three aces to pace Pierce College to 
a 15-8, 15-13, 15-13 victory over Santa Barbara City in a women's Western State 
Conference volleyball match Tuesday at Pierce. 
</P>
<P>
Pierce (16-1 overall, 15-1 in conference play) will play for the conference 
title Friday at Cuesta. 
</P>
<P>
In another WSC volleyball match: 
</P>
<P>
Ventura d. Moorpark, 15-10, 15-10, 8-15, 15-10 -- Nikki Ferreria had 12 kills 
for host Moorpark (6-10 in conference play). Christa Grenat and Danielle Larson 
each added 10 kills for Moorpark. 
</P>
<P>
GIRLS' TENNIS 
</P>
<P>
Kennedy 6, Chatsworth 1 -- Kennedy (15-5, 5-5) swept all four singles matches 
in a West Valley League match. Chatsworth fell to 10-4, 6-4. 
</P>
<P>
GIRLS' VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
<P>
Santa Barbara d. Newbury Park, 15-12, 15-8, 15-12 -- Shane Donnellon had 14 
kills to lead host Santa Barbara (15-5) in a Southern Section 5-A Division 
wild-card match. Newbury Park finished 11-4. 
</P>
