<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and Wire reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taggart Reportedly Got $50,000 from Lincoln: Former California Savings and Loan 
Commissioner Lawrence W. Taggart received a $50,000 consulting fee from 
now-defunct Lincoln Savings &amp; Loan within a week after he left office, the 
San Francisco Chronicle reported. The check was written 27 days after Taggart 
approved a request by Lincoln involving $900 million in taxpayer-insured 
deposits, the newspaper said. Taggart has denied wrongdoing in the case. 
</P>
</TEXT>
