<TEXT>
<P>
The average baseball salary last season increased 19.8% to $586,816, according 
to a study by management's Player Relations Committee. 
</P>
<P>
It was the largest increase in one year since 1982. 
</P>
<P>
The study showed that the Kansas City Royals had the highest payroll in 
baseball, $23,617,090. The Boston Red Sox were second at $22,713,698, followed 
by the San Francisco Giants at $22,456,224, the Oakland Athletics at 
$22,274,834 and the New York Mets at $22,154,333. 
</P>
