<HEADLINE>
<P>
HOLLYWOOD FALL MEETING OPENS 37-DAY RUN TODAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BILL CHRISTINE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Hollywood Park's fall meeting, which includes five major races during its 
37-day run, opens today with the $60,000 Allez France Handicap at 1 1/16 miles 
on grass. 
</P>
<P>
With a Wednesday-through-Sunday schedule, plus Monday racing on Veteran's Day, 
Nov. 12, and closing day, Dec. 24, Hollywood will have a first post of 1 p.m., 
with the exception of 11 a.m. on Thanksgiving, Nov. 22, and 12:30 p.m. on Dec. 
24. 
</P>
<P>
Jose Santos, the New York jockey who plans to stay in California through the 
Santa Anita winter season, has landed the mount on Daughter of Wolf, a longshot 
in the Allez France. Santos, the national money champion for four straight 
years, trails Gary Stevens by about $500,000 in the standings this year. 
Stevens is riding Invitation Waltz, an English filly making her American debut, 
in the Allez France. BILL CHRISTINE 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
SCHEDULES; HOLLYWOOD PARK RACE TRACK; HORSE RACING 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
