<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; 
</P>
<P>
VASQUEZ TO BE GUEST IN FRENCH PROGRAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Orange County Supervisor Gaddi H. Vasquez leaves Friday for an all-expense-paid 
trip to France, where he will spend two weeks, courtesy of the French 
government, participating in a new cultural exchange program. 
</P>
<P>
Vasquez is one of no more than 10 Americans who will participate in France's 
Invitational Cultural Exchange Programme, begun last year. 
</P>
<P>
Participants are chosen because they "show promise of a brilliant future" in 
their careers within their own countries, according to the French Consulate. 
</P>
<P>
Vasquez chose his own subjects to study while in France: local and regional 
government, public transit, national health care and environmental policies. 
</P>
<P>
He said he expects to gain "invaluable insight into French custom and 
governmental operations." 
</P>
<P>
The French government began the program to teach Americans about France "beyond 
the traditional cliches," according to the consulate. 
</P>
<P>
Vasquez will meet with Admiral Philippe de Gaulle, a senator and the son of the 
former French President Charles de Gaulle. 
</P>
</TEXT>
