P.M. BRIEFING; 
</P>
<P>
GM PLANS CZECH OPEL ASSEMBLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DETROIT 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
General Motors Europe said today it plans to assemble vehicles and produce 
transmissions at the Bratislavske Automobilove Zavody (BAZ) facilities in 
Bratislava, Czechoslovakia, pending the outcome of talks. 
</P>
<P>
GM Europe said from its Zurich headquarters that initial plans call for the 
manufacture of up to 250,000 automobile transmissions a year for export to 
other GM facilities in Europe, as well as the assembly of Opel passenger cars 
for sale in Czechoslovakia. 
</P>
<P>
Production could begin in late 1992, GM said. The auto maker is also in the 
process of establishing a distribution organization for selling Opels in the 
Slovak Republic. 
</P>
<P>
Following recent developments in Eastern Europe, GM has already established a 
facility for assembly of the Opel Vectra in Eisenach, Germany. Production began 
in early October. 
</P>
