<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
BUONICONTI TO GET CAMP AWARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW HAVEN, Conn. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Nick Buoniconti, a former Notre Dame All-American and All-Pro linebacker, was 
selected the 1990 Walter Camp Man of the Year. 
</P>
<P>
"He has been a great football player, he has attained outstanding success in 
both law and business and he has contributed immensely to the betterment of 
mankind in his role as a major fund-raiser and supporter of the Miami Project 
to Cure Paralysis," said Kevin O'Brien, Walter Camp Football Foundation 
president. 
</P>
<P>
The Miami Project is an effort to find ways to cure paralyzing spinal injuries. 
Buoniconti has raised millions to finance the project since a football injury 
left his son, Marc, a Citadel linebacker, a quadriplegic. 
</P>
<P>
Buoniconti will receive the award at the 24th Annual Walter Camp All-America 
Banquet on Feb. 16 at Yale University. 
</P>
