SHORT TAKES; 
</P>
<P>
HOMETOWN TO HONOR JUDDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ASHLAND, Ky. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Naomi and Wynonna Judd will return to their hometown for the renaming of the 
16th Street Plaza in their honor. 
</P>
<P>
The mother-daughter singers, recipients of the Country Music Assn.'s Duo of the 
Year award for seven straight years, will be honored Nov. 20. The plaza will be 
renamed Judd Plaza. 
</P>
<P>
The pair, whose hits include "Mama, He's Crazy" and "Grandpa," will also serve 
that day as grand marshals of a Christmas Parade. 
</P>
<P>
Naomi Judd has announced plans to retire after their latest concert tour 
because of hepatitis. Her daughter will continue a solo career. 
</P>
</TEXT>
