SHORT TAKES; 
</P>
<P>
DONAHUE FOCUSES ON E. ST. LOUIS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
EAST ST. LOUIS, Ill. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Phil Donahue heads to this once-prosperous Mississippi River town to ask, "Can 
Anything Be Done to Save This Dying City?" 
</P>
<P>
The "Donahue" show will be taped Monday at a high school here. 
</P>
<P>
The New York-based syndicated program will look at the transformation from a 
national rail and stockyard center to "a desolate and dying city," spokeswoman 
Alyssa Schwartz said. 
</P>
<P>
"Thousands of jobs have gone with the closing of factories, leaving the city a 
pocket of hopeless poverty, trash-strewn vacant lots, block after block of 
boarded-up houses, and crime and drugs running rampant," Schwartz said. 
</P>
<P>
No date has been selected for the segment to air nationally. 
</P>
</TEXT>
